-- Anglo, AngloGold, BHP, Lonmin May be Active: South Africa Stock Preview
-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 2010-12-20T05:56:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-19/anglo-eastplats-lonmin-south-africa-stock-market-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  fell for the
first day in four, losing 0.2 percent to 31,631.07 in
Johannesburg.  Anglo American Plc  (AGL SJ): The platinum, palladium and
nickel miner may buy the Oppenheimer family out of diamond
company  De Beers , the Sunday Times reported, citing unidentified
people. Anglo gained 3.13 rand, 1 percent, to 333.33.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd.  (ANG SJ): Gold for immediate
delivery gained 0.7 percent to $1,384.55 an ounce at 9:35 a.m.
in Singapore as demand from users halted a decline. AngloGold
fell 16.68 rand, or 4.8 percent, to 329.32 rand.  Gold Fields
Ltd.  (GFI SJ) declined 4.18 rand, or 3.3 percent, to 121.72
rand.  BHP Billiton Plc.  (BIL SJ): Copper climbed for a second
day, gaining as much as 2.1 percent to $9,257.50 a metric ton on
the London Metal Exchange, on speculation that a strengthening
U.S. economy will boost the outlook for the metal. BHP Billiton
fell 1.51 rand, or 0.6 percent, to 266 rand.  Eastern Platinum Ltd.  (EPS SJ): Workers at Eastern
Platinum’s Barplats mine are demanding appointment of more black
people in management positions. The shares were unchanged at
11.95 rand.  Lonmin Plc  (LON SJ): The world’s third-largest platinum
producer is scheduled to resume talks with the National Union of
Mineworkers to resolve a wage dispute. The shares gained 99
cents, or 0.5 percent, to 200.99 rand.  The following shares begin trading without the rights to
their latest dividends:  African & Overseas Enterprises Ltd. (AOVP SJ); Bips
Government Inflation Linked Bond Fund (BIPINF SJ); Bips Top 40
(BIPS40 SJ); Dorbyl Ltd (DLP1 SJ); Life Healthcare Group
Holdings Pty. Ltd. (LHC SJ); Rex Trueform Clothing Company Ltd.
(RTOP SJ).  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) remained unchanged at $24.34.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) gained 0.7 percent to $48.23. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) dropped 0.6 percent to $77.86. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) advanced 1.1 percent to $4.81. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) jumped 0.6 percent to $17.75. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) remained unchanged at $12.34. Impala Platinum Holdings
Co. (IMPUY US) advanced 1 percent to $32.87. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
declined 0.2 percent to $4.99. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) rose 0.6
percent to $48.76. Telkom South Africa Ltd. (TLKGY US) advanced
2.8 percent to $21.50.  To contact the reporter on this story:
